[On July 4, 2025, the One Big Beautiful Bill Act (“OBBBA”) was signed into law. The legislation makes permanent several provisions of the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act, including 100% bonus depreciation for certain qualified property, and reverses the requirement under the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act to capitalize and amortize domestic research and experimentation expenses, allowing taxpayers to deduct such expenses in the year incurred for tax years beginning after December 31, 2024. The OBBBA also includes modifications to the U.S. international tax framework. In accordance with ASC 740, the effects of changes in tax law must be recognized in the period of enactment.

Although the provisions were enacted after the end of the reporting period, we are currently evaluating their impact and anticipate a material effect on our future consolidated financial statements. We will recognize the tax law effects in the third and fourth quarter of 2025, the period of enactment.]
